com.androidrecord.query
Class QueryContext<T extends ActiveRecordBase>

java.lang.Object
  com.androidrecord.query.QueryContext<T>

public class QueryContext<T extends ActiveRecordBase>
extends java.lang.Object

Each time the user runs a query, it is executed in its own context to resolve all the one-to-one associations for that record. One-to-many associations are lazily loaded and are handled differently.

See Also:
